<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>bon mot • good word</xh5><p> <i>bon mot</i>—(Fr.) is used to refer to a clever, often biting, joke or witticism: “The luxuries of the mansion have been transferred to the hovel,” he laughed, pleased with his <u>bon mot</u>.</p><p><i>good word—</i>favorable opinion about a person as conveyed to his potential employer, etc.: I beg you to say a <u>good word</u> for me to your father. He regards me, I believe, as a very light fellow...</p> </entry>
